  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a user, i'd like to be able to define what interface the engine API should listen to.\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Remove all references to http-rpc flags\r\n2. Observe that the engine api by default hooks to ``127.0.0.1``\r\n3. Add the ``--rpc-http-host`` and ``--rpc-http-enabled=false``\r\n4. Observe desired behavior\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** I find (3) to be an anti-pattern.  Needing to define a flag not related, then disable it, even get a log statement for it being ignored, yet it affects the outcome.  Not right.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** A defined flag to serve the purpose described.\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: ``22.7.1``",
